<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/6994888-anna"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1394152961i/6994888._UY100_CR5,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/6994888-anna">Anna</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">This is a slow, intense, complex novel, and even though I always read at a pretty high level, I do not think I could have handled this book at 15. It&apos;<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">This is a slow, intense, complex novel, and even though I always read at a pretty high level, I do not think I could have handled this book at 15. It's not inappropriate because of sexual content or violence, but because I think you have to have read a little more and been challenged by reading a little more before you can really dive into and appreciate it. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
